{
  "texts": [
    "To enhance the function-calling capability of xLAM-7b-fc-r and xLAM-1b-fc-r, we employ a targeted training approach, with 50% of their training data drawn from our high-quality synthetic functioncalling dataset.",
    "The remaining 50% of the data is sampled from other tasks within our training set.",
    "For Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) (Rafailov et al., 2023), we prompt less powerful models to generate and rate responses for selected data from each source, then sample a subset for human verification.",
    "After adjustments to models and prompts, we classify the selected responses as rejected samples.",
    "We use a supervised fine-tuning (SFT) approach, further aligning model checkpoints with the DPO method, and leverage the robustness of our flexible data pipeline."
  ]
}